Certiorari Denied.

(See also Nos. 352 and 353; and Nos. 102, 103, 139, and 142, Misc., supra.) No. 325. United States v. Landman, Superintendent of the Five Civilized Tribes; and Landman, Superintendent of the Five Civilized Tribes, v. United States. No. 327. Solicitor General Perlman for the United States, petitioner in No. 325 and respondent in No. 327. With him on the brief in No. 327 were Assistant Attorney General Caudle, Helen B. Carloss and Lee A. Jackson. Huston Thompson and Oscar P. Mast for petitioner in No. 327.

Certiorari denied.
